        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 3:35PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mount Auburn, or 14 miles north of Taylorville, moving southwest at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Auburn.
</description>
